This was our first stop while bar hopping in Harlem. It was really busy but we found bar seats. The drinks were good and strong and the bartenders were really nice! We stayed for a good while and ended up ordering some guacamole.  We had some interesting and almost intrusive guests that wouldn't stop talking to us but other than that, we had a pretty good time. I'd come back next time I'm in town!

One of my favorite bars in Harlem. Great casual atmosphere. The bar tenders are all super friendly. They offer cheese balls with drinks upon request. And they serve and adult happy meal for $10 which includes a can of beer, shot, and hot dog. Seriously...what more could a gal want?

Mess hall is cool. Mess hall does not care what you want it to be, it just does what it wants to do. Mess Hall serves great craft beer and imaginative cocktails and gourmet hot dogs. Mess hall has this nerdy vibe that instantly inspires you to let your inhibitions down and launch into that discussion of how Hayek really was quoting Marx when he rap battled Keynes. Mess Hall has an outdoor porch in the back, where you can polish your own rap battles and present at one of Mess Hall's open mic nights!

The beer and cocktail program are good (not great), but with that said they are among the best in the neighborhood.  This is a cool spot to hangout, when it's not too crowded.

Adult Happy Meal. That will be enough to get you through the door. Movies projected onto brick walls.  One restroom in the entire bar, but to be expected for its size. Hot dogs, cheese puffs, and popcorn oh my... Very slim sustenance menu but worth the price of admission and comparable to the size of the establishment.  During the warner months an outdoor area is available.  The crowd is different depending on the night - ranging from the college crowd,  after work set or anything that resembles what the neighborhood residents currently resemble.
